-- Russian Technologies, Metalloinvest to Study Platinum Mining
-- B y   J a k e   R u d n i t s k y
-- 2012-06-27T18:31:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-27/russian-technologies-metalloinvest-to-study-platinum-mining.html
State-owned Russian Technologies
Corp., Russian billionaire  Alisher Usmanov ’s Metalloinvest and
Telconet Capital signed a partnership agreement to pursue
international mining projects.  The partners will study the creation of a consortium to
mine, process and sell platinum group metals, according to a
statement sent by e-mail from Usmanov’s mining company today.  Russian Technologies may provide  Zimbabwe  with military
helicopters in exchange for the possible participation in a
platinum mining venture in the African nation, Kommersant
newspaper reported today, citing a person in the Russian
presidential administration whom they didn’t identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jake Rudnitsky in Moscow at 
 jrudnitsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
